<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="271" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="4.[136,1452,728,1294]" pageId="4" pageNumber="271">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,342,728,754]" pageId="4" pageNumber="271">Diagnosis:—</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authorityName="I. Zafar, Afshan &amp; Khalid" authorityYear="2022" box="[342,632,728,754]" class="Leotiomycetes" family="Erysiphaceae" genus="Phyllactinia" kingdom="Fungi" order="Erysiphales" pageId="4" pageNumber="271" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="himalayensis">
<emphasis box="[342,632,728,754]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="271">Phyllactinia himalayensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is distinguished from the phylogenetically allied species 
<taxonomicName box="[1276,1403,728,754]" class="Leotiomycetes" family="Erysiphaceae" genus="Phyllactinia" kingdom="Fungi" order="Erysiphales" pageId="4" pageNumber="271" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="betulae">
<emphasis box="[1276,1403,728,754]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="271">Ph. betulae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[136,278,764,790]" class="Leotiomycetes" family="Erysiphaceae" genus="Phyllactinia" kingdom="Fungi" order="Erysiphales" pageId="4" pageNumber="271" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="linderae">
<emphasis box="[136,278,764,790]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="271">Ph. linderae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by its large-sized chasmothecia, up to 280 µm diam., rather shorter appendages, 68‒184 µm, small ascospores, 10‒20 × 7‒13 µm, and its distinct position in the phylogenetic analysis.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
